snippet.textDisplay:
BAN ALCOHOL
*Family problems.
*Violence.
*Un-lawful behavior.
*Poor work ethics.
*Lack of respect for the community.
*Lack of respect for them-self.
*A burden on the medical system and tax payer.
*Lost days of work and play, loss of memory.
*Fines
*Loss of income.
*Lack of promotion.
*Damage to your self and others, most mentally and physically.
*Criminal activity.
*Death
If your partner is a heavy drinker, you can expect all of the above.
If you are an alcoholic or heavy drinker or if the booze is in control of your life, you need to address that.
It's time to ban alcohol, it only causes problems and has no place in a modern society.
In this case, we need to see a very long jail term and restitution for the family.

RIP children.
Our hearts go-out to the families affected.

snippet.textDisplay:
You can have all the penalties you want but it won't make any difference if someone wants to drink and drive.
It's all in the mind of each individual.
Do you think a drunk person cares about a penalty if they are in an intoxicated state?
They couldn't care less.
This is all comes down to selfishness and lack of consideration and concern for others.
Which is why I say you should never get drunk because it affects your personality, ethics, boundaries, and decision making.
In this case, the results are devastating and this act has caused someone immense suffering that will last for years.
This man will never get over it.
He will only learn to live with it.
Not only him but his immediate family, friends and relatives also.
I'm sure the drink driver didn't do this on purpose but he will need to pay the price for his reckless actions.
I wish the family comfort and peace during this time.
